 Email hacking scams are on the increase. Money intended to be paid as the purchase price of property, transfer costs and fees are the target of online theft. Hackers gain access to the email accounts of the seller, purchaser or the conveyancing attorneys and use the addresses to communicate fraudulent banking details. Parties are usually unsuspecting as they expect the emails and the emails form part of an existing chain of correspondence. The unsuspecting victim ends up paying the fraudster instead of the intended recipient. To avoid falling victim to these scams experts recommend the following measures: Contact our professional team on Tel 041 5019800 for assistance on your property related matters. 